    <briefdescription>
<para><ref refid="class_mochi_1_1_f_s_1_1_pack_file" kindref="compound">PackFile</ref> is a class with two purposes. First, it implements <ref refid="class_mochi_1_1_f_s_1_1_i_file_loader" kindref="compound">IFileLoader</ref>, allowing to be used as a simple file system. Second, it has the Pack and Unpack methods, used to create .pak files, used by this file system. Creating .pak files has several benefits. The first one is obfuscation, making it more difficult to end users to get access to your game assets. The second one is being loaded as a stream, as it allows to only load what is needed at the moment. It also is easily extended to, for example, zip all or only specific files, reducing final build size. Ownership: </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>It takes ownership of the point in memory where the pak file is. However, it is created as a stream and not loaded fully on initialization. Guarantees:</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>If the file exist at the specified path and is a valid pak file, the metadata will be loaded and the pack open. Thread safe:</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>GetFile is not thread safe, as it uses a single handler to seek and read data. Check <ref refid="_i_file_loader_8h_source" kindref="compound">IFileLoader.h</ref> for more info on the interface methods. </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
